
Overview of noun sage

The noun sage has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) sage -- (a mentor in spiritual and philosophical topics who is renowned for profound wisdom)
2. (1) sage -- (aromatic fresh or dried grey-green leaves used widely as seasoning for meats and fowl and game etc)
3. sage, salvia -- (any of various plants of the genus Salvia; a cosmopolitan herb)

